<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-13T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-13T11:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.9318/128: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-13T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 13,
                                        1928—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>311. It is the desire of the War Department to have a report as to
                            whether, from the point of view of the Minister, the troops and agencies
                            of the United States Army in China have fulfilled the expectations of,
                            and been satisfactory to, the Department of State. It is requested that
                            the Minister prepare and transmit such a report, as soon as he returns
                            from leave.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>